Huge amount of "dead space" between Marcy Avenue and Union Avenue. We need to use this space better (DOT plaza program...) The "triangle" is about 1/3 the size it could be. We should expand the triangle or do a CitiBike station in the striped street space where there is no concrete poured. This area, too, in incredibly in need of more transit options, as the G is the closest subway. Bike share will be critical for residents in Marcy Houses. There should be a push made to do serious, culturally relevant outreach to BK neighbors who have not yet had access to bike share in the past. Affordability rates should be promoted, and the Citibike station here should include improvements to the pedestrian, planted triangle in general. CitiBike station here would open up this form of transportation to the SatMar community, as well. This area is a critical "meeting of neighborhoods" (Bushwick, BedStuy, South Williamsburg), and a bike share station here could start to open up some public space for social exchange & sharing -- two things that neighbors are hard-pressed to find in the Broadway Triangle. We can seriously improve connectivity (social and transportation) is this area, and siting a CitiBike station here would be a laudable first step.
